iptables-update is a composable solution for managing firewall rules. It reads
rules from data files in /etc/sysconfig/iptables.d and updates
/etc/sysconfig/iptables with additions and removals. Upon completion, it runs
'service iptables reload'.

templates/el6/iptables/iptables-update
* adds and removes iptables rules using /etc/sysconfig/iptables-update.d
* provides a firstboot service for handling clean install under anaconda

templates/el6/iptables/iptables-update-client.xml
* template for clients (e.g. templates/el6/httpd/httpd-config.xml) to require
the iptables-update utility, install firewall rules, and run iptables-update
on package updates and removal. See the template for additional iformation.

templates/el6/iptables/iptables-update-test.xml
* template for testing iptables-update operation

templates/el6/iptables/iptables-update.xml
* template for installing the iptables-update utility.

templates/el6/iptables/iptables-update.definition
* template for testing iptabtes-update installation and updates.
